stylometry:
The variables that must be considered are how long is lead time, how much is demand, is demand constant, if demand is not constant; what affects it, how much is costs to store the safety stock vs. how much money will be lost if we run out of product early.
The amount of lead time is important because we need enough safety stock to cover how long it takes for the next order to arrive. The demand determines how much product we expect to need during lead time. If the demand changes we must attempt to predict when these changes will happen in order to alter the safety stock amount. We also must consider how much it costs to store safety stock in comparison to how much profit we will lose by not having enough product. If it costs $3000 to store a safety stock valued at $2500 and we would only lose $150 by not having enough product, it would not be beneficial to keep a full saftey stock.
